Project history

PsySuite 2.0 is a modular Android framework for implementing and running
psychophysical experiments on smartphones and tablets.

The present application module is a brand new module developed while working in 

Life Science Computational Lab (LISCOMP)
IRCCS Azienda Ospedaliera Metropolitana
Genova, Italy (2024–2026).

that uses both a new library module (psysuitepython) and deeply re-engineered modules (psysuitecore, psysuitetests, nativeaudio) derived from old modules implemented when he worked in the
Unit for Visually Impaired People (U-VIP),
Fondazione Istituto Italiano di Tecnologia (IIT),
Genova, Italy (2018–2021).



Author and developer: Alberto Inuggi

